<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Morphological description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Frustule disciform, valve face flat, 9.4-14.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
in diameter, multiseriate striae 10-14 in 10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
, ribs are continuing on curve of the valve, spines grow from every rib (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7" captionText="Figure 7. SEM (A-E, G, H) and LM images (F) of species found in the transitional zone at Mykolaiv city, valve views: A Cyclotella cryptica B Cyclotella marina C, D Cyclotella meduanae E, F Cyclotella meneghiniana G Cyclostephanos dubius H Cyclostephanos invisitatus, with arrows shown on A, D, H marginal and central fultoportulae, B marginal fultoportulae, F central fultoportulae. Scale bars: 2 μm (B, D); 4 μm (A); 5 μm (C, E); 10 μm (F-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.178.64426.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/545739" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">7H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="ecology">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Ecology.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName authority="" authorityName="" class="Bacillariophyceae" family="Stephanodiscaceae" genus="Cyclostephanos" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Cyclostephanos invisitatus" order="Thalassiosirales" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="invisitatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Cyclostephanos invisitatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded as planktonic species from rivers, ponds, lakes, reservoirs and seas, freshwater, brackish and marine waters. Also known from waters of eutraphentic conditions, moderate and higher trophy and moderate alkalinity (
<bibRefCitation author="Krammer, K" journalOrPublisher="Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, Berlin" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B75" refString="Krammer, K, Lange-Bertalot, H, 2000. Bacillariophyceae. Bd. 2., Teil 3: Centrales, Fragilariaceae, Eunotiaceae. Suesswasserflora von Mitteleuropa. Spektrum Akademischer Verlag, Heidelberg, Berlin" title="Bacillariophyceae. Bd. 2., Teil 3: Centrales, Fragilariaceae, Eunotiaceae. Suesswasserflora von Mitteleuropa." year="2000">Krammer and Lange-Bertalot 2000</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Siver, A" editor="Lange-Bertalot, H" journalOrPublisher="Annotated Diatom Iconographs. 14. A. R. G. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 463" refId="B113" refString="Siver, A, Hamilton, PB, Stachura-Suchoples, K, Kociolek, JP, 2005. Diatoms of North America: The Freshwater Flora of Cape Cod, Massachusetts, U.S.A. In: Lange-Bertalot, H, Ed., Iconographia Diatomologica. Annotated Diatom Iconographs. 14. A.R.G. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell: 1 - 463" title="Diatoms of North America: The Freshwater Flora of Cape Cod, Massachusetts, U. S. A." volumeTitle="Iconographia Diatomologica." year="2005">Siver et al. 2005</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-009-9993-4" author="Kirilova, EP" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Applied Phycology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B68" refString="Kirilova, EP, Cremer, H, Heiri, O, Lotter, AF, 2010. Eutrophication of moderately deep Dutch lakes during the past century: Flaws in the expectations of water management? Hydrobiologia 637(1): 157-171. https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-009-9993-4" title="Eutrophication of moderately deep Dutch lakes during the past century: Flaws in the expectations of water management? Hydrobiologia 637 (1): 157 - 171." url="https://doi.org/10.1007/s10750-009-9993-4" year="2010">Kirilova et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Hofmann, G" editor="Metzing, D" journalOrPublisher="Band 7: Pflanzen. Landwirtschaftsverlag, Muenster, Naturschutz und Biologische Vielfalt 70 (7)" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="601 - 708" refId="B57" refString="Hofmann, G, Lange-Bertalot, H, Werum, M, Klee, R unter Mitarbeit von Koenig C, Kusber, W-H, Metzeltin, D, Reichardt, E, 2018. Rote Liste und Gesamtartenliste der limnischen Kieselalgen (Bacillariophyta) Deutschlands. In: Metzing, D, Hofbauer, NL, Hajek, GM, Eds., Rote Liste gefaehrdeter Tiere, Pflanzen und Pilze Deutschlands. Band 7: Pflanzen. Landwirtschaftsverlag, Muenster, Naturschutz und Biologische Vielfalt 70(7): 601 - 708" title="Rote Liste und Gesamtartenliste der limnischen Kieselalgen (Bacillariophyta) Deutschlands." volumeTitle="Rote Liste gefaehrdeter Tiere, Pflanzen und Pilze Deutschlands." year="2018">Hofmann et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="31" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
<taxonomicName genus="C." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Chromista" lsidName="C. invisitatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" phylum="Ochrophyta" rank="species" species="invisitatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="31">C. invisitatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found 5 km downstream Mykolaiv city (Table 
<tableCitation captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="T1" captionText="Table 1. Species composition of centric diatoms at the investigated sites near Mykolaiv city in the Southern Bug River in the year 2017 (2013 added for station 2)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" tableUuid="DD3AC92F3D14B9FD95B22148C16CA677">1</tableCitation>
), and was recorded for this River earlier (
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/S1642-3593(12)70205-7" author="Bilous, O" journalOrPublisher="Ecohydrology &amp; Hydrobiology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="211 - 230" refId="B10" refString="Bilous, O, Barinova, S, Klochenko, P, 2012. Phytoplankton communities in ecological assessment of the Southern Bug River upper reaches (Ukraine). Ecohydrology &amp; Hydrobiology 12 (3): 211 - 230, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/S1642-3593(12)70205-7" title="Phytoplankton communities in ecological assessment of the Southern Bug River upper reaches (Ukraine)." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/S1642-3593(12)70205-7" volume="12" year="2012">Bilous et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1127/1863-9135/2014/0509" author="Bilous, O" journalOrPublisher="Fundamental and Applied Limnology" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="277 - 295" refId="B11" refString="Bilous, O, Barinova, S, Klochenko, P, 2014. The role of phytoplankton in the ecological assessment of the Southern Bug River middle reaches (Ukraine). Fundamental and Applied Limnology 184 (4): 277 - 295, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1127/1863-9135/2014/0509" title="The role of phytoplankton in the ecological assessment of the Southern Bug River middle reaches (Ukraine)." url="https://doi.org/10.1127/1863-9135/2014/0509" volume="184" year="2014">Bilous et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1615/InterJAlgae.v18.i4.70" author="Belous, EP" journalOrPublisher="International Journal on Algae" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="377 - 386" refId="B8" refString="Belous, EP, 2016. Phytoplankton taxonomic structure of the lower part of the Southern Bug River (Ukraine). International Journal on Algae 18 (4): 377 - 386, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1615/InterJAlgae.v18.i4.70" title="Phytoplankton taxonomic structure of the lower part of the Southern Bug River (Ukraine)." url="https://doi.org/10.1615/InterJAlgae.v18.i4.70" volume="18" year="2016">Belous 2016</bibRefCitation>
). In turn, it is common for the Dnipro River and there are some findings in the Danube River (
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="31">
Probably a cosmopolitan species, known from Europe (Germany, Hungary, Poland, Russia), Asia (Armenia, Azerbaijan, Russia), Northern America (USA), Africa (Egypt); Caspian Sea (
<bibRefCitation author="Wojtal, AZ" journalOrPublisher="Polish Botanical Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="177 - 207" refId="B135" refString="Wojtal, AZ, Kwandrans, J, 2006. Diatoms of the Wyzyna Krakowsko-Czestochowska upland (S. Poland) - Coscinodiscophyceae (Thalassiosirophycidae). Polish Botanical Journal 51 (2): 177 - 207" title="Diatoms of the Wyzyna Krakowsko-Czestochowska upland (S. Poland) - Coscinodiscophyceae (Thalassiosirophycidae)." volume="51" year="2006">Wojtal and Kwandrans 2006</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsarenko, PM" journalOrPublisher="Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B127" refString="Tsarenko, PM, Wasser, SP, Nevo, E, 2009. Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A.R.A. Gantner Verlag, Ruggell" title="Algae of Ukraine: diversity, nomenclature, taxonomy, ecology and geography. Vol. 2. Bacillariophyta. A. R. A." year="2009">Tsarenko et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-011-0067-0" author="Kiss, KT" journalOrPublisher="Acta Botanica Croatica" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" pagination="311 - 363" refId="B69" refString="Kiss, KT, Klee, R, Ector, L, Acs, E, 2012. Centric diatoms of large rivers and tributaries in Hungary: Morphology and biogeographic distribution. Acta Botanica Croatica 71 (2): 311 - 363, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-011-0067-0" title="Centric diatoms of large rivers and tributaries in Hungary: Morphology and biogeographic distribution." url="https://doi.org/10.2478/v10184-011-0067-0" volume="71" year="2012">Kiss et al. 2012</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Genkal, SI" journalOrPublisher="Filigran, Yaroslavl" pageId="0" pageNumber="31" refId="B45" refString="Genkal, SI, Kulikovskiy, MS, Kuznetsova, IV, 2020. Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]. Filigran, Yaroslavl" title="Modern freshwater centric diatom algae in Russia [Sovremennye presnovodnye centricheskie diatomovye vodorosli Rossii]." year="2020">Genkal et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
